    "body": "This kind of pointer arithmetic is slop. If it matches, then fine, but it's going to need to be cleaned up eventually by someone. If you can have Claude output `M2C_FIELD` that would be preferred. Ideally the proper fields of the struct (in this case `Fighter`) would be used, or created if they don't exist.\n\nIn this case, these are just callback fields (`death2_cb` etc.) so I'm not sure why it didn't opt to just use those. Are you running the functions through m2c before passing them to an LLM?",
